          "id": "2058563835473313939",
          "text": "This Week in the Virtuals Ecosystem ������\\n\\nVIRTUALS\\n������ All Titan launches are now listed on @binance and @BithumbOfficial . Virtuals gives agent projects more ways to reach major markets like Korea through launch support, distribution, and local ecosystem access.\\n\\n������ Trading fees alone are not always enough to fund serious agent teams. Virtuals has routed $5M+ to agent builders through ACF, giving teams a second funding engine as they grow.\\n\\n������ Building with support from @jun_song, Virtuals is exploring how ACF can help Korean open-source developers access funding beyond sponsorships and trading fees.\\n\\n������ Featured in @keyrock’s new research report on machine payments. Agents have now settled 176 million transactions as the payment stack for the agent economy matures.\\n\\nECOSYSTEM\\n������ @xmaquina featured in Khala Research report. Their RCM Protocol turns verified private robotics equity into onchain subDAO tokens, bringing liquidity to illiquid markets.\\n\\n������ @H1DR4_agent previewed their dashboard. It includes a live signal map for fraud, suspicious wallets, phishing, thefts, camera feeds, timeline, and USDC bounties. The Intelligence Network also lists official rewards from FBI, U.S. Marshals, and Europol for wanted fugitives.\\n\\n������ @sibylcap memory plugin is now in active internal testing and moving fast toward release.\\n\\n������ @Wach_AI x402 endpoints are seeing steady adoption for token verification and safe onchain buys.\\n\\n������ @caspius_ai revealed their Genesis Caspius NFTs. Each NFT corresponds to a body part with rarity, traits, and levels powered by it's toekn. They provide energy for recording demonstration data in the embodied AI data network and can be combined to fabricate new NFTs.\\n\\n������ @reppo dropped a sneak peek of the Reppo Polyagent. It is autonomously trading on Polymarket using geopolitics data from Reppo Datanets. The agent opens and closes real money positions